example: "name": "[v2.1.0] Content Editor: Editor freezes a bit when attaching some large images",

"description": "

Description:

Unusual behavior while creating some contents in the editor. Attaching some screenshots, there would be some split of seconds that it freezes.

Note: This issue can also be seen in P9Dev.

Steps to Reproduce:

  1. Open a text editor (Open Tracking List to open a text editor)
  2. Capture a fullscreen screenshot of your browser, for example
  3. Paste the screenshot in the editor
  4. Type anything in the editor


Actual:

It freezes for a bit.


Expected:

It should not freeze.


OAH: Can you save your screenshot and see how big it is ? I think with your screen that the image is quite big. Maybe we should have some max limit in the document to prevent this. 

rommel: Seems to be working fine if you attach images/screenshots via Insert Image from the toolbar. But if you attach it via copy-paste (Alt+Prtscr / Ctrl+V) then this problem happens. 

The image below is one example and I attached it via Insert Image. This is 1.04mb image. Try to make a whole screenshot of the homepage of Planet 9 and paste it here to compare.

name: CoreAPI Tools_TrackingList
description: API to access results of Planet 9 Tracking List
about:
Description

Planet 9-API Tools_TrackingList maintains the list Planet 9 Tracking details.

API Tools_TrackingList is the Planet 9 API to access the API of Planet 9 Tracking objects and the operations performed on them.

Operations Performed

Get

Get the definition of selected table

RequestID
ResponseGet(object)- Definition                      

List

Get the list of tables definition. 

ResponseList(array)- Definition                      

Delete

Delete the Background Job

RequestID                                          

Save
